WEBVTT

00:01.086 --> 00:03.359
Denny, somehow I've grown
rather fond of Shirley.

00:03.359 --> 00:05.908
Well, you can't have her.
A man doesn't eat where his friend…

00:05.908 --> 00:07.211
–Schmidts?
–Exactly.

00:07.211 --> 00:10.620
The fact is, many HMO's
are outsourcing major surgery.

00:10.620 --> 00:12.812
When a person is told
she needs heart surgery,

00:12.812 --> 00:15.196
she does not expect to be
shipped to India to have it.

00:15.196 --> 00:17.532
Judge Marcia Hooper
was found murdered last night.

00:17.532 --> 00:18.646
We were having an affair.

00:18.646 --> 00:20.733
–What's going on?
–The police just arrested Scott Little.

00:20.733 --> 00:22.947
<i>–Maybe I should do it.
–You mean, kill judge Hooper?</i>

00:22.947 --> 00:24.175
He's talking to a therapist.

00:24.175 --> 00:26.786
You gave the tape to the police
the afternoon of her death?

00:26.786 --> 00:28.964
Well, I gave it to her husband.

00:28.964 --> 00:30.211
What?

00:37.914 --> 00:41.062
No, no, no, no, we're not
gonna be making any statements.

00:41.062 --> 00:42.792
It hurts me way more
than it hurts you.

00:42.792 --> 00:44.461
You know how much I love to talk.

00:44.461 --> 00:48.533
Let's just say we're very happy that
Scott Little is out of that jail cell,

00:48.533 --> 00:50.675
a place he shouldn't
have been to begin with.

00:51.169 --> 00:55.256
<i>The fact that they would let
an accused killer out at all</i>

00:55.256 --> 00:59.544
<i>goes to show what a joke our
criminal justice system has become,</i>

00:59.544 --> 01:04.890
<i>where the haves get one form of justice
and the have-nots get none at all.</i>

01:05.039 --> 01:07.381
Denny, you have got
to gag this woman.

01:07.381 --> 01:10.302
–I would love to.
–Evidently, she plans to attend the trial.

01:10.302 --> 01:11.649
Gracie Jane's coming to Boston?

01:11.649 --> 01:13.649
Well, she lost John Mark Karr.

01:13.759 --> 01:15.482
I am a nervous wreck.

01:15.482 --> 01:17.756
It doesn't matter
how many trials I do.

01:17.756 --> 01:20.069
Every one is like the first one.

01:20.069 --> 01:20.963
Who's he?

01:20.963 --> 01:23.572
Paul Lewiston, Bethany Horowitz.
We're in trial together.

01:23.572 --> 01:26.214
It all comes down
to opening arguments, you know?

01:26.214 --> 01:29.732
80% of all trials, the jury makes up
its mind after the opening.

01:29.732 --> 01:31.992
You shouldn't smoke.
It'll stunt you.

01:31.992 --> 01:33.785
Um, never mind.

01:34.205 --> 01:36.894
What, you've never seen
a smoking dwarf before?

01:36.894 --> 01:38.652
Bethany, are you okay to do this?

01:38.652 --> 01:40.057
Of course I'm okay.

01:40.057 --> 01:41.740
I just get opening-day jitters.

01:41.740 --> 01:43.840
You know what I do
when I get anxious?

01:43.840 --> 01:46.857
–No, and I don't want to know.
–It works.

01:47.197 --> 01:52.717
You are a sicko, perverted,
lewd, disgusting sleaze.

01:52.717 --> 01:54.763
It's sexual, this ear pinch.

01:54.763 --> 01:57.600
Yes. Pinching the ear
gives you blood flow.

01:57.600 --> 02:01.017
When's the last time you got that
without taking a pill?

